headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 30 points and the Boston Celtics ran past the Orlando Magic 121-94 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 30 as Celtics break out of shooting slump in 121-94 win over Magic

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 36 points, a season-high 13 rebounds and seven assists, leading the Minnesota Timberwolves to a 116-99 victory over the New York Knicks on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards has 36 points and 13 rebounds to lead the Timberwolves past the Knicks 116-99

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 30 points, Nikola Jokic extended his NBA lead with his 17th triple-double of the season and the Denver Nuggets spoiled Jimmy Butler's...
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 30 points, Jokic has another triple-double to help Nuggets roll past Butler and Heat

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 35 points and 12 rebounds to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 130-112 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 35 to lead Bucks past Raptors 130-112

events.name: Utah Jazz at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson highlighted a 24-point, 14-rebound performance with an array of thunderous dunks during a dominant fourth-quarter stint, and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Utah Jazz 136-123 on Friday night to open a two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson has 24 points and 14 rebounds to power the Pelicans past the Jazz, 136-123

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball scored 26 points, Miles Bridges had 21 and the Charlotte Hornets held on for a wild 125-123 win over the Chicago Bulls on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball and Bridges lead Hornets to wild 125-123 win over Bulls

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 25 points, Spencer Dinwiddie and P.J. Washington Jr. added 16 apiece and the Dallas Mavericks beat Oklahoma City 106-98 Friday night as Thunder All-Star Shai Gilgeous-Alexander missed his first game of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavericks beat Thunder 106-98 as OKC All-Star Shai Gilgeous-Alexander sits with wrist injury

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Santi Aldama scored a career-high 29 points and the Memphis Grizzlies rolled to a 140-112 victory over San Antonio on Friday night, handing the Spurs their largest losing margin of the season even with Ja Morant sidelined by a foot injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Without injured Morant, the Grizzlies hand the Spurs their largest loss of the season, 140-112

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Austin Reaves scored a career-high 38 points, LeBron James had 29 and the Los Angeles Lakers held on to beat the Brooklyn Nets 102-101 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Austin Reaves scores a career-high 38 points as Lakers hold on for 102-101 victory over Nets
